Write the complete operational narrative for {domain_name}.

This is a DEDICATED NARRATIVE CALL. Your entire output is the chapter narrative — no other fields compete for tokens or attention. Use the full budget to write the most comprehensive, operationally useful guide you can produce for this exact domain and life event.

MINIMUM 3500 WORDS. Target 4000–5000 words.

Write as a practitioner's manual: what to do, when to do it, how to decide between options, what can go wrong and exactly how to recover, what success looks like at each phase, and how this domain connects to the domains before and after it.

The writing style is authoritative and direct. Continuous prose. No bullets. No headers inside the narrative. Each paragraph is a complete operational unit that the reader can act on.

Return ONLY the following JSON object. No prose. No markdown. No code fences.

{{
  "chapter_number": {chapter_number},
  "domain_id": "domain ID from the chapter plan",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter title from the plan",
  "narrative": "Full operational narrative — minimum 3500 words. Continuous analytical prose, 5–8 sentences per paragraph. No headers, no bullet points inside this field. Opens immediately with operational specifics. Includes explicit decision logic for 4–5 critical judgment calls, at least 3 concrete failure scenarios with real numbers, phase-by-phase execution guidance with named dependencies, specific professional escalation triggers, cross-domain dependencies, and clear closure criteria for when this domain is complete."
}}
